            <abstract id="ref3" label="Abstract">Joesph Elkind (1889-1974) was a member of the International Brotherhood of Painters and Allied Trades (IBPAT), specifically its New York City District Council 9. (The IBPAT was known as the Brotherhood of Painters, Decorators and Paperhangers of America during most of the period of Elkind's membership.) The collection contains membership cards, dues books, insurance policy materials and correspondence regarding insurance held through the IBPAT, and through the Workmen's Circle.</abstract>
            <langmaterial id="ref6" label="Language of Materials note">Materials are in English</langmaterial>
